# Cluster Safety

## Never Run Without Asking

Before executing any of the following against the cluster, **stop and ask the user for approval**. Do not proceed on your own.

- `DELETE`, `UPDATE`, `DROP`, `TRUNCATE` SQL statements via `oc exec deploy/postgres`
- `oc delete` of any resource (pods, deployments, secrets, configmaps, PVCs)
- `oc scale` to zero replicas
- `oc rollback` or `oc rollout undo`
- Any `POST` or `DELETE` to admin API endpoints (`/api/admin/*`)
- `npm run deploy` or `deploy.sh` — the user deploys, not the agent

## Safe to Run Without Asking

- `SELECT` queries against the database (read-only)
- `oc get`, `oc describe`, `oc logs` (read-only inspection)
- `GET` requests to any API endpoint
- `oc exec ... node -e "fetch(...).then(...)"` for read-only API calls

## When Proposing Destructive Operations

1. State exactly what will be changed and how many rows/resources are affected
2. Provide the command for the user to copy and run themselves
3. Wait for explicit confirmation before executing
